                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.119/352: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-09-23T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 23—2:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>266. Department’s no. 237, September 15. At present moment claim that American
                    companies are discriminated against and that embargo on arms to China is dead
                    letter is much exaggerated. Violations of embargo so general, however, by
                    nationals of all nations that yesterday I proposed to Legations of France, Great
                    Britain, and Japan that a new declaration be made of embargo on arms. Identic
                    telegram is being drafted by French Legation to be sent by the Ministers to
                    their respective Governments. …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
